premise_source_doc_sentence: Kosovo  (  -LSB- ˈkɒsəvoʊ , _ ˈkoʊ - -RSB- Kosova , -LSB- kɔsɔva -RSB- or Kosovë ; Косово  )  is a disputed territory and partially recognised state in Southeastern Europe that declared independence from Serbia in February 2008 as the Republic of Kosovo  (  Republika e Kosovës Република Косово / Republika Kosovo  )  .
